    <gsw_content_information action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <article><![CDATA[<p>Set the <em>x_taniu_tan_core.tanium_username</em> system property to the username for a Tanium service account with full access to anything you might want to use or do via Tanium Integration Core, from ServiceNow.</p>
<p>Next, set the <em>x_taniu_tan_core.tanium_password</em> system property to the password for the Tanium user account username indicated in the <em>x_taniu_tan_core.tanium_username</em> property.</p>
<p>It may be wise to limit this service account&#39;s access to only what it needs to do. <br />For assistance with configuring this &#34;least-privilege&#34; access, please contact your TAM. </p>
<p>If using the API Token, this step may be skipped. However, it&#39;s recommended to specify both username/password, <em>and</em> API Token, as that makes automated API token rotation possible. </p>
<p>This system property is stored using 2-way encryption so that it&#39;s encrypted at rest. </p>]]></article>
